            "answer_text": "Yes! You have to write the compulsory Kannada language test in KPSC if you have studied Kannada as a third language in your 10th standard. One can avoid writing the compulsory Kannada language test only if he/she has, Studied in Kannada medium school.Or should have studied Kannada as 1st or 2nd language in their 10th/higher education.Or Kannada language should have been chosen as an elective in their higher education examination.If you can provide documents or markscards to support any of the above three points, you may not write the compulsory Kannada language test. Hope this helped. Edit 1: Adding screenshots from few notifications.   As you can see, there will be minor changes in the requirement from department to department. Hence, check the notification of the exam you are applying to know the exact requirement. ",
